text: The earthquake struck at about 9:30 a.m. and had a depth of 2.7 miles, according to the USGS. The quake was centered about two miles from The Geysers and 13 miles east of Cloverdale. Earlier this morning, an earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 2.0 struck near The Geysers, according to the USGS. The earthquake struck at about 7:30 a.m. and had a depth of 1.4 miles, according to the USGS.
title: An earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 4.4 struck in Sonoma County this morning near The Geysers, according to the U.S. Geological Survey.
